<dl id="n14055c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14055c">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14055c"> 55(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the divine&apos;s comedy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the same manner did Goethe feel repelled by the &ldquo;<mark>Divine Comedy</mark>.&rdquo; &ldquo;To my mind,&rdquo; he says, &ldquo;the picture of Hell is horrible; that of Purgatory equivocable, and that of Paradise dull&rdquo; (July 20, 1787). <small> Ernst Boldt, <a name="BFLS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BFLS"><cite title="source">From Luther to Steiner</cite></a>, (1921) 25</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05231g" href="c05all.htm#c05231g">VI.C.05:231(g)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
